<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,710]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,418,443]" pageId="3">Collecting site.</emphasis>
Nerudová-Horsáková collected 
<specimenCount box="[765,873,418,443]" pageId="3" type="adult">
<number box="[765,793,419,443]" pageId="3" value="87.0">87</number>
adults
</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[924,1043,418,443]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbata">
<emphasis box="[924,1043,418,443]" italics="true" pageId="3">P. limbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above herbaceous vegetation on 
<date box="[151,265,452,476]" pageId="3" value="2001-06-01">
<number box="[151,161,452,476]" pageId="3" value="1.0">1</number>
.VI. 
<number box="[202,265,452,476]" pageId="3" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</date>
at Velká Klajdovka, a limestone steppe near Brno, 
<collectingCountry box="[843,1026,452,477]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="3">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
. At this site, 
<taxonomicName box="[1172,1286,452,477]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbata">
<emphasis box="[1172,1286,452,477]" italics="true" pageId="3">P. limbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was the only 
<taxonomicName box="[151,296,485,510]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Sciomyzidae</taxonomicName>
species collected. Curiously, all individuals were found on a very limited portion of the large steppe area where the grass 
<taxonomicName box="[404,611,518,543]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="valesiaca">
<emphasis box="[404,611,518,543]" italics="true" pageId="3">Festuca valesiaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Schleich ex. Gaudin) (
<taxonomicName box="[896,991,519,543]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
) is the dominant vegetation. The soil around the base of each plant was densely inhabited by the terrestrial snail 
<taxonomicName authority="Draparnaud, 1801" authorityName="Draparnaud" authorityYear="1801" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" genus="Granaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="frumentum">
<emphasis box="[1039,1276,552,576]" italics="true" pageId="3">Granaria frumentum</emphasis>
(Draparnaud, 
<number box="[151,208,585,609]" pageId="3" value="1801.0">1801</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
(Gastropoda: 
<taxonomicName box="[388,542,585,610]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Chondrinidae</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[572,652,585,610]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1322,1344]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,756,1291]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,744,1300]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pherbellia limbata. A, adult female (from Hungary). B, Granaria frumentum, ventral view. C, idem, lateral view. Photo A provided by G. Keresztes from Hungary; Photos B and C provided by J-C. Vala." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258833/files/figure.png" pageId="3">
Figs. 
<number box="[641,652,585,609]" pageId="3" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B, C). In terms of ecology, this snail is restricted to xerothermic limestone steppes. Other terrestrial snails found at this site included some individuals of the rare species 
<taxonomicName authority="Ferussac, 1821" authorityName="Ferussac" authorityYear="1821" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Cepaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vindobonensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3">Cepaea vindobonensis</emphasis>
(Férussac, 
<number box="[457,514,652,676]" pageId="3" value="1821.0">1821</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[545,658,652,677]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Helicidae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Draparnaud, 1801" authorityName="Draparnaud" authorityYear="1801" box="[686,1177,652,677]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hygromiidae" genus="Euomphalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="strigella">
<emphasis box="[686,931,652,677]" italics="true" pageId="3">Euomphalia strigella</emphasis>
(Draparnaud, 
<number box="[1112,1169,652,676]" pageId="3" value="1801.0">1801</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Menke, 1828" authorityName="Menke" authorityYear="1828" class="Gastropoda" family="Hygromiidae" genus="Xerolenta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="obvia">
<emphasis box="[1249,1436,652,677]" italics="true" pageId="3">Xerolenta obvia</emphasis>
(Menke, 
<number box="[252,309,686,710]" pageId="3" value="1828.0">1828</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
(the latter both 
<taxonomicName box="[496,649,685,710]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hygromiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="3" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Hygromiidae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
